model

Class Conference

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • model.Conference

  • public class Conference
extends java.util.Observable
    Conferences store the Conference object's unique ID number, name, the assigned Program Chair, a description of the Conference, the start and end dates of manuscript submission and the Conference itself and the location. Two constructors used depending on whether a new Conference is being added TO the database or it's being recreated FROM the database at the start of a new user session.
    Version:
    2 June 2014
    Author:
    Trevor Jennings

    • Constructor Detail

      • Conference

        public Conference(int theID,
          java.lang.String theName,
          User theProgramChair,
          java.sql.Date thePaperStart,
          java.sql.Date thePaperEnd,
          java.sql.Date theConferenceStart,
          java.sql.Date theConferenceEnd,
          java.lang.String theLocation,
          java.lang.String theDescription)
        Constructor for Conference that already exists in database. For example, the Conference was created in a previous Session and has an ID as persistent date in the database. When a User logs off, then logs on again sometime later, this Conference object needs to be recreated (Conference objects are not persistent).
        Parameters:
        theID - the Conference's ID
        theName - the Conference's name
        theProgramChair - the Conference's Program Chair
        thePaperStart - the Conference's Date for accepting Manuscripts.
        thePaperEnd - the Conference's Date for no longer accepting Manuscripts.
        theConferenceStart - the Conference's start Date.
        theConferenceEnd - the Conference's end Date.
        theLocation - the Conference's location.
        theSession - the current Session. Used for security as Users with AccessLevel less than that of a Program Chair cannot create a Conference.

      • Conference

        public Conference(java.lang.String theName,
          User theProgramChair,
          java.sql.Date thePaperStart,
          java.sql.Date thePaperEnd,
          java.sql.Date theConferenceStart,
          java.sql.Date theConferenceEnd,
          java.lang.String theLocation,
          java.lang.String theDescription)
        Constructor for a Conference being created for the first time. In other words, there is no persistent date representing this Conference in the database. In this case, the Constructor's ID is not passed as a parameter (it does not yet exist) but rather is generated and assigned by calling the method createConference() from the ConferenceControl class.
        Parameters:
        theName - the Conference's name
        theProgramChair - the Conference's Program Chair
        thePaperStart - the Conference's Date for accepting Manuscripts.
        thePaperEnd - the Conference's Date for no longer accepting Manuscripts.
        theConferenceStart - the Conference's start Date.
        theConferenceEnd - the Conference's end Date.
        theLocation - the Conference's location.
        theSession - the current Session. Used for security as Users with AccessLevel less than that of a Program Chair cannot create a Conference.
